John Hightower from Boise State is another WR that could be an option if available. The Cowboys are also believed to be interested in Miami RB DeeJay DALLAS as a potential pick in the later rounds. Deejay Dallas and Tony Pollard who gave fans a glimpse of what he can do with more rushes will take turns and might provide a more versatile offensive scheme with a running back by committee approach.  Just remember you read it here first.

snippet.textDisplay:
The headline aside, what is never discussed is what they, the Pats, have done for the last 20 years- TWENTY YEARS.
They've been at the top of the pile for 20 years.
It's hard enough to win a Super Bowl, when you do, your off season is shorter, recovery is shorter, planning and prep for the upcoming season is shorter.
Yet, they've been doing it for years. Not one everyone of them, but in the thick of it.
That in and of itself is nothing short of amazing..
Brady and Belichick's preparation is benchmark..
Sure they fell short yesterday, but their track record has them on NFL Mt Rushmore.
Enjoy it for what it is/was as you will never see the likes of Brady - Belichick and the Pat's (with them) or anyone else again..

TB’s options:
Pats: but possibly without Josh and a weak draft. Maybe strong free agent pickups for the offense like they did in 2007. Too many maybes
Definite and established teams below:
A grade: Cowboys good RB and Receivers. Jerry Jones would definitely draft to support Brady if he thinks Brady gives him a chance to win a SB. Best offensive line of the three.
B grade: Brady and Josh A grade Cleveland two good RBs, receivers, and TE
B grade: Don’t really like the receivers but their big targets. Chargers two good RBs, receivers, and TE. Chargers will need to keep Gordon
All teams with quality defense
Titans: if they don’t resign Tannehill this fit might work. Has a History wit coach, good RB. Young rising receivers. Good defense. I think would draft to support Brady.

Josh could possibly bring Brady wit him if he leaves, which could help the development of a young QB to be mentored by Brady. If a young QB has the humility to step down and be mentored.

Just my thoughts.
